Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Gambian airspace has been closed to commercial airlines since 23 March in an effort to contain the spread of coronavirus . There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from The Gambia.
British government special flights
Booking for UK special flight for British tourists, short term visitors and their direct dependents to return to the UK on 30 April is now closed. There are currently no plans for further special flights from The Gambia to the UK.
This travel advice will be updated if future departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts. You can also register your details with us at ukinthegambia@fco.gov.uk.
Follow the British High Commission Banjul on Twitter and Facebook for more details.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and you have exhausted all other options available to you for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan to cover the cost of the ticket. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
If you are vulnerable and have registered your details with the High Commission, you may receive a call about these flights. To protect you from scams, callers will identify themselves to you using personal information you have already submitted to the High Commission.
Travel to the airport
For those who have been notified of your ticket, you will receive an email explaining the check-in arrangements at the airport. You will receive guidance on how to travel to the airport and you will need to organise your own travel there. You must arrive at the airport by 1:10pm on Friday 30 April.
Arrival in the UK
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
If you cannot leave The Gambia
If you cannot leave The Gambia at this time, you should:
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus
find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs.
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
if your visa is close to expiring contact the Immigration Department for advice
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission on 00220 449 5133/ 449 4508 and ukinthegambia@fco.gov.uk.
The High Commission cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
